<h2 id="bstarting-with-basic-initializationb">&lt;/b&gt;Starting with basic Initialization&lt;/b&gt;</h2>

<p>The first thing you will do is change the name of the blog or change the image and delete some pseudo-posts</p>

<p>Former is simple, you just delete files under _posts tab and change the contents in config.yml.</p>

<p>Next, I deleted some of the contents in _layout/home.html, and changed background img</p>

<p align="center">
<img align="center" height="400" src="/img/posts/githubpage/home_html.png" />
</p>

<p>Now my main page looks like this:</p>

<p align="center">
<img align="center" height="400" src="/img/posts/githubpage/start.png" />
</p>

<p>I am planning to put my own feature into the main page later.</p>

<hr />

<h2 id="badding-additional-linkb">&lt;/b&gt;Adding additional Link&lt;/b&gt;</h2>

<p>I would like to add additional content at top bar that links to my Github.</p>

<p>Under _includes, there is a file named “navbar”.html</p>

<p><img align="center" height="400" src="/img/posts/githubpage/navbar_.png" /></p>

<p>Add</p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>
&lt;li class="nav-item"&gt;
&lt;a class="nav-link" href="https://github.com/hslrock"&gt;Github&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;

</code></pre></div></div>
<p>in amy position. The result will be:</p>

<p><img align="center" height="50" src="/img/posts/githubpage/navbar.png" /></p>

<p>Next we will discuss the organizing the posts into different categories</p>
